did.unittitle: Institute for Management Science and Engineering records
did.abstract: Materials in this collection include logistics research, technical papers, conference publications and books. The collection covers the years 1948 to 1987.

prefercite.head: Preferred citation
prefercite.p: Institute for Management Science and Engineering records, Special Collections Research Center, The George Washington University.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: Acquisition data is unknown for this collection.

userestrict.head: Restrictions on Use
userestrict.p: Some material may be copyrighted or restricted. It is the patron's obligation to determine and satisfy copyright or other case restrictions when publishing or otherwise distributing materials found in the collections.

bioghist.head: Historical or Biographical Note
bioghist.p: The Institute for Management Science and Engineering was a part of School of Engineering and Applied Science. This institute is no longer fuctioning.

scopecontent.head: Collection Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: Materials in this collection include logistics research, technical papers, conference publications and books. The collection covers the years 1948 to 1987.

otherfindaid.head: Other Finding Aids
otherfindaid.p: Detailed finding aid created by Principle Investigator (1956-1987) William H. Marlow can be found here.

odd.p: correspondence, technical memoranda, , Serial Numbers 72233 - 73125. Note printouts of log books for "Series 70000" and ASCII files therefor on diskettes in Box 17. An early organizational plan is also included
